items.htmlTitle: Earliest deadline first scheduling - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
items.snippet:
Earliest deadline first (EDF) or least time to go is a dynamic scheduling algorithm 
used in real-time operating systems to place processes in a priority queue.
